6078#message">www.mobhunter.com/message...78#message</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Developers Forum:<br>Poisons will not be revamped. The Developers feel that Rogues are just fine the way they are right now and do not need an increase in power (which &quot;fixing&quot; poisons would give them).<br><br>The skill bonuses that objects give, such as +5% Dodge, +10% Dodge, are not cumulative. Much like haste items, the game engine will give you the highest bonus that any one item has. (In the case of the dodge example above, you would receive the 10% Dodge bonus.) This limitation *INCLUDES* tradeskill modifiers. So, if you thought you were getting away with something by holding both a tinkered tradeskill modifier object in addition to a tradeskill trophy that has the same type of modifier, the game engine only chooses the highest percentage modifier. It will not add the two together.<br><br>Per Conversation with Scott Hartsman:<br>Horses are semi-broken. If you are sitting upon a horse and have invisibility cast upon you, mobs that do not normally see invis will still be able to see you, regardless of the fact that their con message may read &quot;indifferent&quot;. This is low on the priority list of things that should be fixed.<br><br>A new enhancement will be added to the game. A graphical compass will be added to the UI, although I am unclear as to whether this will be a feature of the Planes of Power release or something that comes out earlier. The accuracy and responsiveness of the graphical compass will be in direct relation to how high of a sense heading skill you have. <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadiabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadia brell</A>